==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tumefy
<hw>Tu"me*fy</hw> <pr>(t⟦umac⟧"m⟦esl⟧*f⟦imac⟧)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Tumefied</conjf>
<pr>(t⟦umac⟧"m⟦esl⟧*f⟦imac⟧d)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Tumefying</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F. <ets>tum⟦eacute⟧fier</ets>,
fr. L. <ets>tumere</ets> to swell + <ets>-ficare</ets> (in comp.) to
make; cf. L. <ets>tumefacere</ets> to tumefy. See <er>Tumid</er>, and
<er>-fy</er>.]</ety> <def>To swell; to cause to swell, or puff
up.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To swell, <qex>tumefy</qex>, stiffen, not the diction only, but
the tenor of the thought.</q> <rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tumefy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tumefy
<hw>Tu"me*fy</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To rise in a tumor; to
swell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tumescence</ent>⟦br⟧
